lready terminated and couldn't accept incoming messages.\n\nThe cron session continued processing after the timeout and exited, so the issue was logged but the session itself remained stable. Now comparing against the last heartbeat state from around 13:24 UTC, the critical sessions are still running: the 5p QLHV cron is active, the DTLX cron is active, and the Agent Status cron is running.\n\nChecking the current timestamp of 13:38 UTC, I can see cron:e7885813 did fire and updated its state, so there's been some activity in that session since the last check.\n\nLooking at the broader session landscape, the Agent Status cron encountered a delivery timeout when trying to reach the Lead's direct session, but that session was already done anyway—the message delivery was attempted after the fact. The cron itself continues running normally.\n\nThe key distinction here is that the timeout was a delivery attempt failure to an already-terminated session, not an actual system failure, so it's not a new blocker or critical issue worth reporting.\n\nNow I'm reviewing the session updates across the board—the cron jobs are firing normally on schedule, and the subagent failures are all pre-existing from previous runs with no new failures detected. The delivery timeout to Lead was already documented, so nothing here warrants a change report. I'll stay silent and update the heartbeat state."},{"type":"text","text":"Silent exit — no new changes detected. All sessions stable since last cycle.\n\n**Heartbeat state update:** 13:38 UTC, 3 active crons, no new failures, no new blockers. Pipeline healthy."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":30087,"output":661,"totalTokens":45108,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":416,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776173922677,"responseId":"062d7663ef93fe506148ed27b0486dce","__openclaw":{"id":"1a99d2f4","seq":5}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","