ctual new failures, new sessions spawned, or blocked tasks. From what I can see, the only real change is that the Agent Status cron finally delivered after being stuck, and there are no new failures to report.\n\nActually, wait—I should double-check the session keys. The cron:e7885813 entry in the heartbeat state might be a different session from the one I see in the current list, since the formats don't quite match up. Let me verify what's actually running before I decide whether to stay silent. Looking at the session timestamps, the Agent Status cron sent a report at 13:34 UTC while the current cycle is at 13:41 UTC—a 7-minute gap, though the cron runs every 10 minutes so this is expected timing. Comparing the current state to the last heartbeat, I'm seeing the same three cron jobs running, the same three done sessions, and no new failures or sessions spawned.\n\nThe only change is that cron:ac986a8d shifted from stuck to done, which actually indicates progress rather than a problem. Since all critical pipelines remain active with no new failures, I'll stay silent and update the heartbeat timestamp.","thinkingSignature":"51e739d95eac026a8f1669febb33ef072000fe491a55ad8101669d2ebb4f2db1"},{"type":"text","text":"Silent exit — no new changes detected. All sessions stable since last heartbeat (10:59 UTC).\n\n**Heartbeat state update:** 13:41 UTC. 3 active cron sessions (5p-DTLX, 5p-QLHV, Agent Status), no new failures, no new sessions, no blockers. Pipeline healthy."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":629,"output":1165,"cacheRead":33045,"cacheWrite":173,"totalTokens":35012,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776174099340,"responseId":"062d771411dd81a7adacd287042b97b3"}}
